						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">3gengames wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">It probably uses MMC3 IRQ's to do those, editing the X on hit. DWIII also does that and so does Rad Racer, but they don't use MMC3 IRQ's because they're MMC1. I don't know how they do it, probably timed code.</div>
<br />Ninja Gaiden doesn't use MMC3 either (it's MMC1). So it pretty much has to use timed code. Seems to use sprite 0 hit for the determine where to start the effect, though.
<br />
<br />BTW OP, it's impossible to get multiple sprite 0 hits per frame, as 1) it's not possible to move sprites in the middle of the frame without disabling rendering 2) it's not possible to clear the sprite 0 hit flag manually, it gets cleared at the end of the vblank</div>

					
