			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">For cutscenes and whatever other screens that are not actual gameplay you can usually get away with a sprite 0 hit for the first split and timed code for the rest. Easier than monkeying around with DMC IRQs, IMO.
<br />
<br />During gameplay things are not so simple... depending on the amount of processing needed for different parts of the levels you might miss the sprite hit (i.e. you start waiting for it after it has already happened, causing the split to happen at the wrong position), and you can't waste much CPU time with timed code.
<br />
<br />In this case, DMC IRQs help, as long as the split point is always the same, otherwise only mapper IRQs can offer a completely stable solution.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

