				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">A work around to wasting CPU time is to make fixed-time code that accomplishes something useful to your engine. This is usually hard to pull off efficiently, since routines in an engine should usually be designed to only process as much information as they need to at a time rather than a fixed amount. But still, you could in theory make use of the time rather than wasting it with NOPs.</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.freewebs.com/the_bott/" class="postlink">-Owner of Poultry Games</a></div>
