					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Celius wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">A work around to wasting CPU time is to make fixed-time code that accomplishes something useful to your engine. This is usually hard to pull off efficiently, since routines in an engine should usually be designed to only process as much information as they need to at a time rather than a fixed amount. But still, you could in theory make use of the time rather than wasting it with NOPs.</div>
<br />I tried this only once, and this is extremely, I mean REALLY extremely hard to do. Especially if you want to support both PAL and NTSC timings...
<br />
<br />If you have to wait a long while and have to do something that can be done in constant timing, it's ok to design the task so that it takes a constant time to be executed and then wait the remaining time which is also constant.
<br />However if you want to do special write every so many scanline and interleave some unrelated calculations between the writes, this becomes a total nightmare.</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Life is complex: it has both real and imaginary components.</div>
