					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Even the Atari 2600, which required the use of raster effects to get <em>anything</em> to display, had a port called WSYNC that when written to would cause the CPU to wait for hblank. A "two-line kernel" could update the screen on one line, do some calculations on the second line, and then STA WSYNC to soak up any excess cycles.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

