<br />I once had an idea that it would be cool to have a special compiler that could automatically build the 6502 code to do tasks like that. You could specify the algorithm you want to run (maybe in a specialized form of 6502 assembly) and what PPU/etc registers you want to write at what times, and it would figure it all out automatically. Of course it would have some limitations, but would be way easier than trying to time everything manually.</div>

